The article discusses a recent strike carried out by US forces against the terrorist group ISIS-K in Afghanistan. The US President states that they will continue to hunt down those responsible for the attack and protect their troops. The situation in Kabul remains dangerous, with a high threat of terrorist attacks on the airport. Despite this, efforts to evacuate civilians from Afghanistan are ongoing. The President pays tribute to the 13 service members who lost their lives and praises their bravery and selflessness.